Dr. Chu SP Okongwu, Nigeria’s former Finance Minister, has passed on.  According to reports, Okongwu died on Wednesday morning in Enugu. He was aged 87. He served as Minister of Finance under the government of General Ibrahim Babangida. He served for eight years in Babangida’s government, firstly as Minister of Finance and National Planning; and subsequently as Minister of Cabinet Affairs and later, Minister of Petroleum. The octogenarian was born on September 23, 1934 in Nnewi, Anambra State. On Sunday, October 3, 2021, some gunmen burnt down Dr Okongwu’s house in his village, Otolo Nnewi. A family source claimed he never recovered from that tragedy.  Source Minna  -    The National Office for Technology Acquisition and Promotion (NOTAP) is set to complement the Federal Government's move to revitalise the economy. NOTAP Director General, Alhaji Danazumi Ibrahim, made the disclosure on Saturday during the organisation’s 2016 management retreat in Minna. He said that NOTAP would align its… In "News" The Federal Executive Council (FEC) on Wednesday gave a minute silence in honour of two former Ministers Senator Bode Olowoporoku and Alhaji Umaru Muhammad Baba. The virtual FEC meeting, which was presided over by Vice President Yemi Osinbajo (SAN), had seven members physically present in the Executive Council Chambers of… In "News" By Emmanuel Oloniruha Abuja   -     The Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) has described  the looters  list released by the Federal Government as part of ploy by the government to divert  people attention  from public discourse. The Party made the observation  in a statement issued by  its Natural Publicity Secretary,  Mr Kola… In "News"